	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hexadecimal">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hexadecimal</a><!-- m -->
<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://computer.howstuffworks.com/boolean1.htm">http://computer.howstuffworks.com/boolean1.htm</a><!-- m -->
<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cpu">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cpu</a><!-- m -->
<br />Stacks: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lifo">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lifo</a><!-- m -->
<br />
<br />Rough instruction summary: 
<br />
<br />-Programs are lists of instructions for the CPU to carry out
<br />
<br />-Load/Store instructions are used to get and put data into registers (memory inside the CPU) or memory (memory outside the CPU)
<br />
<br />-Arithmetic / logical instructions perform operations between registers (particularly the main register--the accumulator) and memory or immediate data
<br />
<br />-Subroutines are used to modularize programs
<br />
<br />-Jump/Branch instructions are used to control the program flow
<br />
<br />----------
<br />
<br />6502 addressing modes: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.obelisk.demon.co.uk/6502/addressing.html">http://www.obelisk.demon.co.uk/6502/addressing.html</a><!-- m -->

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


